Jeh Johnson has been confirmed as the next Secretary of Homeland Security with broad bipartisan support. He is praised for his understanding of the threats the US faces and his ability to work across agencies. Johnson has been a critical member of the national security team and has helped shape successful policies. As Secretary of Homeland Security, he will play a leading role in protecting against terrorist attacks, adapting to changing threats, preparing for natural disasters, strengthening border security, and making the immigration system fairer. The President looks forward to Johnson's counsel and judgment in the future.